title: Toby Keith - Greatest Hits Vol. 1
description:
As a survey of Toby Keith&#039;s first four recordings (not including the seasonal Christmas to Christmas), this set turns in some strong singles, making the case for the Okie singer-songwriter as one of the more traditionally minded of the &#039;90s hat acts. Keith rarely devastates as a singer, but he never overreaches, and there&#039;s more than a bit of grit in his delivery of "Should&#039;ve Been a Cowboy" and "He Ain&#039;t Worth Missing." His emotional triumph remains the obsessive "Who&#039;s That Man," in which Keith sees another man living the life he threw away. Keith also includes two songs not available elsewhere, complementing an appealing mainstream country set.
